In Jerusalem there is also the most sacred place for the Jews, the Wall of Regrets; the remains of a temple destroyed by the Romans in 70 C.E.
As is tradition, people of different religions leave notes here with their desires, which will then come true.
Perform a vertical journey
The ruins of the Masada Fortress were what remained of a secret refuge against the enemies, which Herod the Great commanded to build in 25 B.C. for his family.
