And it is quite well arranged. Sometimes it adds something to reality: here it doesn't all come out so elegantly (the scene in which the crisis at Tehran airport blinds, the diversion of a call to America and the unbridled search after its track becomes crazy).
Argo's weakness is the lack of control that arises from the need to show too much action in too many places.
Alan Arkin and John Goodman have a very funny role as Hollywood collaborators, although their characters deserve more space and are not, much less, the only ones in this film.
